metadata.name: INKED #19
metadata.description:
Inked is the first collection of 'DEFRAG Trilogy' or 'How the machine took over our lives'.

'DEFRAG Trilogy' invites you to think about what your life would be like without all the technology that surrounds us or how digital has taken over our way of thinking.

Inked represents the first contact with the machines and how it can become a painful experience but it stays with us all our lives.

More info about DEFRAG: https://www.fernandojerez.com/site/defrag-trilogy/

metadata.description:
Innocence is the third and last collection of 'DEFRAG Trilogy' or 'How the machine took over our lives'.

'DEFRAG Trilogy' invites you to think about what your life would be like without all the technology that surrounds us or how digital has taken over our way of thinking.

Innocence represents how we live inside a invisible cage. We take our daily tech-pills to kill the pain of living without machines. We totally forgot how it started.

metadata.name: Retrogrades #415
Chord Unknown #179
metadata.description:
The feeling of experimenting with an instrument you have not learned, and then suddenly striking an actual chord.

The code creates several grids and then applies one of six unique deformation techniques with varying intensity. It's a defined process of experimentation, and even though I'm the one that wrote the rules, each output breaks through somehow as a complete surprise to me. So when I see them, I get a Chord Unknown.

Created by Eric Davidson. 2022.
